<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1921,2020]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,271,1921,1948]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Apical expansion of arista 1/4 as wide as long, apically tapering and pointed (
<figureCitation box="[1122,1209,1921,1948]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1902,1927]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,561,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1435,561,1877]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 5. Phortica (Ashima) watabei Sati &amp; Fartyal, sp. nov. (♂ paratype). A, Head (frontal view); B, abdominal sternites; C, periphallic organs (caudal view); D, E, phallic organs (lateral and ventral views, respectively; B-type). Scale bars: 0.1 mm in C–E; 0.5 mm in A, B." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884624" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884624/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
); fore and mid tibiae with dark gray rings proximally and distally (ch.17,18-1); posterior postgonite slightly curved outward, 1/2 as long as anterior one on the same lateral lobe; 2 anterior postgonites on the other lateral lobe widely divergent (
<figureCitation box="[1270,1355,1993,2020]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1902,1927]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,561,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1435,561,1877]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 5. Phortica (Ashima) watabei Sati &amp; Fartyal, sp. nov. (♂ paratype). A, Head (frontal view); B, abdominal sternites; C, periphallic organs (caudal view); D, E, phallic organs (lateral and ventral views, respectively; B-type). Scale bars: 0.1 mm in C–E; 0.5 mm in A, B." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884624" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884624/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 5E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,152,539]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,152,179]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Description</emphasis>
(not repeating characters common to 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Chen &amp; Maca" authorityYear="2012" box="[759,941,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachychaeta">
<emphasis box="[759,776,154,179]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[789,941,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">brachychaeta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Supracervical setae 7–10. Cibarial, medial sensilla approximately 7 per side; posterior sensilla approximately 7 per side. All tarsi with gray tarsomeres IV and V; all tarsomere Is slightly longer than 3 succeeding tarsomeres together.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,152,539]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Measurements (
<typeStatus box="[381,486,261,287]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">holotype</typeStatus>
/ 
<specimenCount box="[495,523,261,287]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="male">1♂</specimenCount>
<typeStatus box="[534,633,261,287]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">paratype</typeStatus>
, in mm): BL = (n/a)/2.06, ThL = 1.27/1.42, WL = 2.50/2.52, WW = 1.13/1.14.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,152,539]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Indices (
<typeStatus box="[300,405,333,359]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">holotype</typeStatus>
/ 
<specimenCount box="[414,442,333,359]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="male">1♂</specimenCount>
<typeStatus box="[454,553,333,359]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">paratype</typeStatus>
, in ratio): FW/HW = 0.41/0.48, ch/o = 0.11/0.09, prorb = 1.17/1.43, rcorb = 0.83/0.53, vb = (n/a)/0.36, dcl = 0.57/0.42, presctl = (n/a)/0.51, sctl = 1.20/1.00, sterno = 0.88/0.92, orbito = 2.00/2.37, dcp = 0.18/0.27, sctlp = 1.50/1.08, C = 2.60/2.31, 4c = (n/a)/1.68, 4v = 2.35/3.11, 5x = 0.75/1.09, ac = 3.10/2.58, M = (n/a)/0.76, C3F = 0.60/0.51.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,152,539]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
The antisymmetry is observed in the postgonites: in A-type, the left lateral lobe bears 2 anterior postgonites, and the right lobe 1 posterior and 1 anterior postgonites; but in B-type, 
<emphasis box="[902,1015,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">vice versa</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1030,1116,512,539]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1902,1927]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,561,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1435,561,1877]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 5. Phortica (Ashima) watabei Sati &amp; Fartyal, sp. nov. (♂ paratype). A, Head (frontal view); B, abdominal sternites; C, periphallic organs (caudal view); D, E, phallic organs (lateral and ventral views, respectively; B-type). Scale bars: 0.1 mm in C–E; 0.5 mm in A, B." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884624" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884624/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 5E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
