<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,152,467]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,297,323]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is unique in having the fore and mid tibiae with gray color rings (ch.17,18-1) within the 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Chen &amp; Maca" authorityYear="2012" box="[151,241,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foliiseta">
<emphasis box="[151,241,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">foliiseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup, and somewhat resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Chen &amp; Maca" authorityYear="2012" box="[651,833,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachychaeta">
<emphasis box="[651,668,334,359]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[681,833,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">brachychaeta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the morphology of the aedeagal sheath and postgonites, but can be distinguished from it by the diagnostic characters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,152,467]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,405,431]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Etymology.</emphasis>
